You're taking a guy's company
underneath him.

00:11:28,810 --> 00:11:32,614
Also, Kevin has offered us
$150,000,

00:11:32,614 --> 00:11:36,451
and then would, uh,
bank us on the other $300,000.

00:11:36,451 --> 00:11:37,285
(Mark) We sit here
all the time and talk about

00:11:37,285 --> 00:11:39,687
how unfortunate
and how tough things are

00:11:39,687 --> 00:11:40,955
in this country right now,
and here we are

00:11:40,955 --> 00:11:44,125
giving the guy a million dollars--
You're stealing
his American dream.

00:11:44,125 --> 00:11:46,361
He's not gonna sell his soul.

00:11:46,361 --> 00:11:49,764
You know,
getting this started

00:11:49,764 --> 00:11:50,398
has been a huge sacrifice
for us.

00:11:50,398 --> 00:11:52,767
Okay.
Okay, Bye.

00:11:52,767 --> 00:11:53,334
(kisses)
Love you.

00:11:53,334 --> 00:11:54,903
All right. (laughs)

00:11:58,006 --> 00:12:00,275
(exhales deeply) Sorry.

00:12:04,779 --> 00:12:06,581
(Kevin) What are you gonna do?

00:12:06,581 --> 00:12:08,149
All right. Um...

00:12:08,149 --> 00:12:11,086
I really think
it's too early in the game

00:12:11,086 --> 00:12:13,188
for us
with the Game Face company

00:12:13,188 --> 00:12:15,056
to give up 100%
of the company.

00:12:15,056 --> 00:12:16,357
Ooh.

00:12:16,357 --> 00:12:20,328
But I do like
Lori and Mark working with us.

00:12:20,328 --> 00:12:26,734
We could go with the $450,000
and $80,000 in salary,

00:12:26,734 --> 00:12:29,504
and we would give out...

00:12:29,504 --> 00:12:32,173
35% equity in the company.

00:12:35,043 --> 00:12:38,012
So, I would like
to counter back, Mark.

00:12:38,012 --> 00:12:42,951
$450,000 at the 40%
that I started with,

00:12:42,951 --> 00:12:46,788
and he can get
the $80,000 salary

00:12:46,788 --> 00:12:48,456
for the first three years.

00:12:48,456 --> 00:12:49,290
I would do
as Lori suggested,

00:12:49,290 --> 00:12:53,761
or $450K for 35%

00:12:53,761 --> 00:12:55,263
plus the $80k guaranteed
for 3 years,

00:12:55,263 --> 00:12:59,834
but a 10% royalty
till we get our money back.

00:12:59,834 --> 00:13:01,169
I'm good with that.

00:13:01,169 --> 00:13:03,438
(Kevin) It just shows you

00:13:03,438 --> 00:13:03,838
my deal is
the right one anyways.

00:13:03,838 --> 00:13:05,206
They're just copying my deal.

00:13:08,309 --> 00:13:12,780
So it's just a question of how
you value the 5% in equity,

00:13:12,780 --> 00:13:14,215
and I'll leave that
up to you.

00:13:14,215 --> 00:13:17,152
(Robert) So, Doug, you've
done something remarkable.

00:13:17,152 --> 00:13:19,654
You've made Mark Cuban grovel.

00:13:19,654 --> 00:13:20,855
(laughs) He has not.
There's no groveling here.

00:13:20,855 --> 00:13:22,257
(Lori laughs)

00:13:22,257 --> 00:13:26,427
♪♪♪

00:13:28,329 --> 00:13:32,534
Well, I like the 35%,

00:13:32,534 --> 00:13:34,135
and I like the 10% royalty
on it.

00:13:34,135 --> 00:13:36,371
So, Mark and Lori...
Let's do it!

00:13:36,371 --> 00:13:38,406
Put your game face on!
Put your game face on, baby!

00:13:38,406 --> 00:13:40,208
Whoo!
Whoo!

00:13:40,208 --> 00:13:42,410
Let's do it!
Let's do it.

00:13:42,410 --> 00:13:45,713
Congratulations, man.
It's gonna be awesome.
Thanks, man.

00:13:45,713 --> 00:13:46,381
We'll have fun.
We'll bring you--

00:13:46,381 --> 00:13:47,949
Bring the kids down
to a mavs game.

00:13:47,949 --> 00:13:51,553
You came here with a company
that makes $30,000 a year,

00:13:51,553 --> 00:13:53,888
and you got a million dollar
value. It's unbelievable.

00:13:53,888 --> 00:13:55,957
Great job. Wow.

00:13:55,957 --> 00:13:59,594
That guy just turned down
a million bucks

00:13:59,594 --> 00:14:00,094
and made you guys counteroffer.

00:14:00,094 --> 00:14:01,963
I was just trying
to solve his problem,

00:14:01,963 --> 00:14:04,465
which was he wanted
security.

00:14:04,465 --> 00:14:06,167
And he wanted to walk the rest
of his life with a soul,

00:14:06,167 --> 00:14:09,270
and I solved that problem.
(laughs)

00:14:09,270 --> 00:14:12,740
I don't think of this
as walking away

00:14:12,740 --> 00:14:13,241
from a million dollars.

00:14:13,241 --> 00:14:18,613
I think of this as walking
towards $20 or $50 million.

00:14:18,613 --> 00:14:19,214
And that's what we're doing.

00:14:19,214 --> 00:14:20,848
We're going towards
the future.

00:14:20,848 --> 00:14:23,851
♪♪♪

00:14:33,661 --> 00:14:34,195
♪♪♪

00:14:34,195 --> 00:14:36,200
My name is Dan Grimm.

00:14:36,200 --> 00:14:39,570
I'm Brant Myers, and we live
in San Luis Obispo, California.

00:14:39,570 --> 00:14:40,137
I met Brant
in fifth grade.

00:14:40,137 --> 00:14:43,800
We played soccer together.
We were in boy scouts together.

00:14:43,800 --> 00:14:46,503
We've been friends
for the past 22 years.

00:14:46,503 --> 00:14:48,605
Ooh!
Come on. Yeah.

00:14:48,605 --> 00:14:50,841
Brant and I love to do
all sorts of things together.

00:14:50,841 --> 00:14:53,577
(whirring)

00:14:53,577 --> 00:14:54,678
Dan and I have always
been tinkerers.

00:14:54,678 --> 00:14:59,549
So it's really no big jump for
us to go into business together.

00:14:59,549 --> 00:15:01,218
He handles one side
of the business

00:15:01,218 --> 00:15:01,918
that I don't want to do.

00:15:01,918 --> 00:15:04,554
I do the things
that he don't want to do.

00:15:04,554 --> 00:15:07,491
(clicking)
between the two of us,
we have one big brain,

00:15:07,491 --> 00:15:09,493
and we can get anything done
that we put our mind to.

00:15:09,493 --> 00:15:11,428
Well, thank you for your order.
All right, Dan.

00:15:11,428 --> 00:15:13,363
We just got another sale.
Let's go celebrate.

00:15:13,363 --> 00:15:13,764
Yeah!
(laughs)

00:15:13,764 --> 00:15:17,300
(Dan) Our product is...

00:15:17,300 --> 00:15:17,934
3-Way split!

00:15:17,934 --> 00:15:20,003
Two of our favorite
pastimes in one.

00:15:21,638 --> 00:15:22,973
When people first see
our product,

00:15:22,973 --> 00:15:25,342
they don't know
what to think,

00:15:25,342 --> 00:15:26,843
they don't know what to say.
They just drool.

00:15:26,843 --> 00:15:27,878
(clink)
Bom.

00:15:27,878 --> 00:15:30,047
Now we need a shark

00:15:30,047 --> 00:15:32,082
to take our product
to the masses.

00:15:34,217 --> 00:15:36,887
♪♪♪

00:15:45,162 --> 00:15:49,366
My name is Dan Grimm,
engineer, gaming nerd.

00:15:49,366 --> 00:15:52,335
I'm Brant Myers,
card-carrying beer connoisseur.

00:15:52,335 --> 00:15:53,870
Our product is the Arkeg.

00:15:53,870 --> 00:15:56,006
And we're offering 33%
of our business

00:15:56,006 --> 00:15:57,974
in exchange for $100,000.

00:15:57,974 --> 00:16:02,412
We had a house in college
with a "kegerator"

00:16:02,412 --> 00:16:04,181
and an arcade game.

00:16:04,181 --> 00:16:04,681
First, we turned
the refrigerator

00:16:04,681 --> 00:16:07,317
into a kegerator.

00:16:07,317 --> 00:16:10,387
Then we fixed up
this old arcade machine

00:16:10,387 --> 00:16:10,787
with parts
laying around the house.

00:16:10,787 --> 00:16:14,191
We found ourselves
staying in on weekends,

00:16:14,191 --> 00:16:14,691
saving a ton of money.

00:16:14,691 --> 00:16:16,827
It was Paradise.

00:16:16,827 --> 00:16:19,429
I went and poured myself
another beer,

00:16:19,429 --> 00:16:22,432
looked back, and saw these
two massive appliances,

00:16:22,432 --> 00:16:22,766
and a lightbulb went on.

00:16:22,766 --> 00:16:26,136
Well, what if,
with my manufacturing expertise,

00:16:26,136 --> 00:16:29,139
and Dan's superb
electronics skills,

00:16:29,139 --> 00:16:29,739
we could create a product
that would combine

00:16:29,739 --> 00:16:31,007
our two favorite pastimes?

00:16:31,007 --> 00:16:32,776
Ladies and gentlemen...

00:16:32,776 --> 00:16:34,744
Let me introduce to you
what has been called

00:16:34,744 --> 00:16:38,248
the greatest invention
of all time...

00:16:38,815 --> 00:16:41,318
the Arkeg!
(laughs)

00:16:41,318 --> 00:16:41,952
Ta-Da!
(laughter)

00:16:41,952 --> 00:16:44,688
Drink...
drink... and game.

00:16:44,688 --> 00:16:47,157
(Lori laughs)
Oh, lord.

00:16:47,157 --> 00:16:47,924
Drink n' game!

00:16:47,924 --> 00:16:49,726
It not only pours
any beer you want,

00:16:49,726 --> 00:16:52,195
but it comes pre-loaded

00:16:52,195 --> 00:16:52,896
with some of the most popular
classic arcade games.

00:16:52,896 --> 00:16:55,465
Is it a fridge?

00:16:55,699 --> 00:16:58,001
It's a keg.

00:17:01,037 --> 00:17:03,106
It doesn't just pour beer.

00:17:03,106 --> 00:17:03,807
How about some wine
for the chef of the house

00:17:03,807 --> 00:17:07,110
after a long day?
(clink)

00:17:07,110 --> 00:17:07,978
(laughing)

00:17:07,978 --> 00:17:11,681
That's how you drink your wine,
Kevin--From a tap.

00:17:11,681 --> 00:17:15,185
Wine's not your thing,
what about some root beer

00:17:15,185 --> 00:17:17,154
for the kids
and their friends?

00:17:17,154 --> 00:17:19,022
Put one
in your family room,

00:17:19,022 --> 00:17:21,158
in your game room,
your man cave.

00:17:21,158 --> 00:17:21,925
Who wants a drink?

00:17:21,925 --> 00:17:25,061
Guys, you're gonna need a drink
when you try to sell these.

00:17:25,867 --> 00:17:27,869
I'm out.

00:17:27,869 --> 00:17:28,336
Whoa!
(Brant) That was fast.

00:17:28,336 --> 00:17:30,071
That's a record.

00:17:30,071 --> 00:17:33,942
Was it the beer, or was it
the game that got you out?

00:17:33,942 --> 00:17:34,309
It was the combination
thereof.

00:17:34,309 --> 00:17:37,579
I just don't see it, guys.
Sorry.

00:17:37,579 --> 00:17:40,615
Wait a minute.
Are you serious with this?

00:17:40,615 --> 00:17:42,517
Absolutely.
It's a great product.

00:17:42,517 --> 00:17:43,952
(Robert) How much is it?

00:17:43,952 --> 00:17:45,487
$4,000 retail.

00:17:45,487 --> 00:17:46,788
(Daymond) Wow.
(Kevin) $4,000?

00:17:46,788 --> 00:17:48,490
Have you sold any of them?

00:17:48,490 --> 00:17:49,190
Absolutely.
We've sold 20.

00:17:49,190 --> 00:17:51,159
(Daymond) You come in here,
guys.

00:17:51,159 --> 00:17:54,696
You're very, very rude.

00:17:54,696 --> 00:17:56,231
You haven't even
offered me a beer.
My apologies, Daymond.

00:17:56,231 --> 00:17:58,533
Wine, root beer, beer?

00:17:58,533 --> 00:17:59,000
Can I pour that thing?
Let me see that.

00:17:59,000 --> 00:18:01,836
(Brant) By all means.
It's actually

00:18:01,836 --> 00:18:03,038
capitalizing
on the current trend,

00:18:03,038 --> 00:18:05,507
which is
pour your own beer.

00:18:05,507 --> 00:18:07,409
What do you got in wine?
Yeah, I'll have a wine.

00:18:07,409 --> 00:18:09,344
It's a 2010 estate Pinot noir
from central coast, California.

00:18:09,344 --> 00:18:11,079
Oh, please, I'll have some.

00:18:11,079 --> 00:18:13,281
Kevin, would like some, uh,
night train or ripple?

00:18:13,281 --> 00:18:16,184
No, no, I'm doing some,
uh, pinot, I think.
(laughing)

00:18:16,184 --> 00:18:17,986
Thank you very much.
Thank you very much.

00:18:17,986 --> 00:18:20,455
Yes.

00:18:20,455 --> 00:18:22,691
I see this as--
As more of a gimmick.
(clink)

00:18:22,691 --> 00:18:26,194
I don't see myself
as being in the Arkeg business.

00:18:26,194 --> 00:18:29,431
I'm out.

00:18:29,431 --> 00:18:31,566
(Robert) I remember
when games like this

00:18:31,566 --> 00:18:33,268
were very, very popular.
So I bought, like, 12 games.

00:18:33,268 --> 00:18:35,770
I put 'em in my basement.

00:18:35,770 --> 00:18:36,871
I thought my friends

00:18:36,871 --> 00:18:38,173
could go down there all the time
and play.

00:18:38,173 --> 00:18:40,008
I gotta tell you,
I haven't been in that room

00:18:40,008 --> 00:18:43,445
for eight years.

00:18:43,445 --> 00:18:46,014
You sold 20 units over 2 years.

00:18:46,014 --> 00:18:48,316
That's low.

00:18:48,316 --> 00:18:51,152
I'm out.

00:18:51,152 --> 00:18:54,489
Guys, I think the beauty
of games now

00:18:54,489 --> 00:18:56,024
is that they're small,
you can play it on your tablet.

00:18:56,024 --> 00:18:58,593
This is just really
a dinosaur.

00:18:59,127 --> 00:19:02,797
I just don't think
it's anything for me. I'm out.

00:19:06,701 --> 00:19:08,903
Mr. Wonderful,
what are you doing?

00:19:08,903 --> 00:19:12,674
I'm, uh, looking at it
as a limited opportunity.

00:19:12,674 --> 00:19:15,577
Not every business
is destined to be huge.

00:19:15,577 --> 00:19:16,378
I prefer to invest
in the ones that are.

00:19:16,378 --> 00:19:18,246
Kevin,
with your capital injection,

00:19:18,246 --> 00:19:20,115
we can get
our price point low enough

00:19:20,115 --> 00:19:22,717
to get into big box stores.

00:19:22,717 --> 00:19:24,686
You're talking about
a high-end refrigerator.

00:19:25,220 --> 00:19:27,022
"look, honey, we can get
an arcade game

00:19:27,022 --> 00:19:29,658
with beer that comes
out of it."

00:19:29,658 --> 00:19:31,493
We have a lot of wives that
buy them for their husbands.

00:19:31,493 --> 00:19:33,628
It's a great--
Listen, guys,
I appreciate the wine,

00:19:33,628 --> 00:19:35,463
and it's actually
quite good.
Thank you.

00:19:35,463 --> 00:19:37,032
I'm gonna take a pass.
I'm out.

00:19:38,166 --> 00:19:40,602
No counteroffer?

00:19:40,602 --> 00:19:43,438
All right, I'll get Lori
to give you $50,000.

00:19:43,438 --> 00:19:44,739
(laughs)

00:19:44,739 --> 00:19:45,807
Lori, we'll take it.

00:19:45,807 --> 00:19:47,942
(laughter)

00:19:47,942 --> 00:19:48,376
Gentlemen, cheers to Arkeg.

00:19:48,376 --> 00:19:50,512
Cheers.
Thank you, guys.

00:19:50,512 --> 00:19:51,680
Good luck, guys.
(Brant) Appreciate it.

00:19:51,680 --> 00:19:52,756
Cheers.
Good luck.

00:19:52,756 --> 00:19:54,925
♪♪♪

00:19:54,925 --> 00:19:57,861
Only on "Shark tank" would you
see that kind of insanity.
(laughs)

00:19:57,861 --> 00:20:00,530
We're disappointed
we didn't get a deal.

00:20:00,530 --> 00:20:03,567
But we get to do what we love.
We're still making money,

00:20:03,567 --> 00:20:05,702
and... we own 100%
of our business.

00:20:05,702 --> 00:20:08,705
♪♪♪

00:20:18,081 --> 00:20:20,350
Next up is Dan Rothwell

00:20:20,350 --> 00:20:23,687
with a product that aims
to make outdoor eating safer.

00:20:23,687 --> 00:20:27,657
♪♪♪

00:20:27,657 --> 00:20:29,559
Hello. My name
is Dan Rothwell,

00:20:29,559 --> 00:20:31,595
and my product is Dura-tent.

00:20:31,595 --> 00:20:36,199
I am seeking $50,000 for a 30%
equity stake in our company.

00:20:36,199 --> 00:20:40,136
Spring is the official start
of picnics and parties

00:20:40,136 --> 00:20:43,273
with family and friends
in the great outdoors.

00:20:43,273 --> 00:20:46,042
But there is nothing
more irritating

00:20:46,042 --> 00:20:48,778
than standing around
swatting the flies

00:20:48,778 --> 00:20:51,948
away from the food,
and rightfully so.
(laughs)

00:20:51,948 --> 00:20:56,052
How many times
have we seen the flies

00:20:56,052 --> 00:20:58,054
hovering around and getting
on that dog poop

00:20:58,054 --> 00:20:59,756
and walking around?
(buzzing)

00:20:59,756 --> 00:21:01,124
Then that fly says...

00:21:01,124 --> 00:21:03,593
(Mark laughs)
"there's a party going on.

00:21:03,593 --> 00:21:05,862
I'm gonna go walk
on that potato salad."

00:21:05,862 --> 00:21:07,764
(laughing)
And it does.

00:21:07,764 --> 00:21:09,866
And it leaves behind
little particulate

00:21:09,866 --> 00:21:12,602
of the disgust it just
picked up along the way.

00:21:12,602 --> 00:21:14,204
Ew.

00:21:14,204 --> 00:21:16,039
Poop potato salad,
anybody?

00:21:16,039 --> 00:21:18,475
No, thank you.
Stop the madness.

00:21:18,475 --> 00:21:19,843
(laughter)

00:21:19,843 --> 00:21:22,946
Let's take a look at a clip
of a fly's day.

00:21:22,946 --> 00:21:26,049
(Robert laughs)
Here's flies swarming
around the garbage.

00:21:26,049 --> 00:21:27,884
Now they stick
their tongue out,

00:21:27,884 --> 00:21:30,587
and saliva goes down, and they
mix it with your food,

00:21:30,587 --> 00:21:33,223
and they suck it up,
and it's disgusting.

00:21:33,223 --> 00:21:37,427
Flies leave behind parasites,
larvae, salmonella,

00:21:37,427 --> 00:21:41,264
and even antibiotic-Resistant
e. Coli.

00:21:41,264 --> 00:21:43,333
The same types of bacteria
that hospitalize

00:21:43,333 --> 00:21:46,136
thousands of people
across the U.S.

00:21:46,136 --> 00:21:47,837
Each and every year,

00:21:47,837 --> 00:21:50,040
and unfortunately,
some of these people die.

00:21:50,040 --> 00:21:53,310
Is this what you want for your
family and friends, sharks?

00:21:53,310 --> 00:21:55,045
No!

00:21:55,045 --> 00:21:56,379
Exactly not.

00:21:56,379 --> 00:21:59,950
Our solution
to this problem

00:21:59,950 --> 00:22:01,851
is the dura-Tent.

00:22:01,851 --> 00:22:04,588
(sharks laughing)

00:22:04,588 --> 00:22:06,623
As you can see,
it's a full enclosure.

00:22:06,623 --> 00:22:08,825
Are we going camping
with that food?

00:22:08,825 --> 00:22:11,261
We're going to the backyard
parties and picnics.

00:22:11,261 --> 00:22:14,264
It's a full enclosure, not just
a little pop-up umbrella.

00:22:14,264 --> 00:22:17,701
A little velcro on the door.
Flip it up, get your food.

00:22:17,701 --> 00:22:19,936
Look at how much food
this protects.

00:22:19,936 --> 00:22:22,372
Easy to clean,
easy to set up.

00:22:22,372 --> 00:22:24,641
My customers love the product.

00:22:24,641 --> 00:22:27,077
With your help,
we can not only make this

00:22:27,077 --> 00:22:29,879
a national success,
but an international success.

00:22:29,879 --> 00:22:31,448
How many have you sold?
50,000 units.

00:22:31,448 --> 00:22:32,983
(Robert) Wow.
Wow.

00:22:32,983 --> 00:22:34,451
Where do you sell them?
How much do they sell for?

00:22:34,451 --> 00:22:36,820
It sells for $19.95--
On my picnic.

00:22:36,820 --> 00:22:39,689
My banquet--Between, uh,
$29.95 and $34.95.

00:22:39,689 --> 00:22:42,592
What's your cost?
My cost is, uh,

00:22:42,592 --> 00:22:46,062
